.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-STATUS 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.9.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-status \- read live and staged Grafana state through a shared status surface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util status [\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
read live and staged Grafana state through one canonical status surface.
.PP
when you want readiness, overview, snapshot, or direct live reads without moving into mutation work.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B live
render a live readiness view from Grafana read surfaces.
.TP
.B staged
render a readiness gate from staged artifacts.
.TP
.B overview
summarize staged artifacts or open the live overview.
.TP
.B snapshot
review or export a snapshot\-style artifact bundle.
.TP
.B resource
inspect one live Grafana resource directly.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
live: render a live readiness view from Grafana read surfaces.
.EX
grafana-util status live --profile prod --output-format yaml
.EE
.PP
staged: render a readiness gate from staged artifacts.
.EX
grafana-util status staged --desired-file ./desired.json --output-format json
.EE
.PP
overview: summarize staged artifacts or open the live overview.
.EX
grafana-util status overview --dashboard-export-dir ./dashboards/raw --alert-export-dir ./alerts --output-format table
.EE
